snippet.textDisplay: I’ve been really sad about the death Kobe and those on the helicopter. However, yesterday my wife showed me a credible news source that Kobe Bryant went to catholic mass with his daughter and prayed. When I saw that post a deep sigh just blew out of me...Carolyn said “aww your happy!”  Truth is, I really am, because to say eternity is important is an understatement. Kobe was a great basketball player and man, and he has been in eternity for over two days now. His death bought the reality of life’s short time to everyone’s front door step. “Tomorrow is not promised” is now embodied in this unexpected event.  Love your children, love your wife, love your family and friends. Most importantly LOVE GOD. Our lives are too short and we have an opportunity to serve Him while we are alive, so let us do our BEST. Jesus lived for a short period of time and changed the entire world because God became a man and died for our sins. I’m so glad he did, so now we can be forgiven and live our lives for Him. Then when our date with death comes, we can see Jesu and be with Him forever. This is so important, because I want ALL of my family there with me! Friends, neighbors, the world, who so ever. Again, I am so happy to hear about Kobe’s  final day beginning with prayer to God. Mambamentality4Jesus 4Real
